  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cities and Infrastructure for Growth Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cities and Infrastructure for Growth Zambia programme (CIGZambia) is a demand-driven facility set up with the objective of providing high-quality technical advice and assistance to Zambian government bodies and private sector organisations. CIGZambia&#x2019;s aim is to engage in projects and programmes that will help harness the potential of Zambia&#x2019;s cities and towns to act as drivers for economic growth and job creation. The main objectives of CIGZambia are to drive economic transformation and job creation in line with the Government of Zambia&#x2019;s 7th National Development Plan. CIGZambia is focused on diversifying the economy, reducing poverty, creating jobs for women and men, building climate resilience, and setting Zambia on a path to becoming a middle-income country. Implemented by Cowater UK Limited, CIGZambia has a Programme Management Unit (PMU) that oversees operations, procurement, finance and administration. The Technical Assistance Fund (TAF) work streams cover the design and implementation of a range of Technical Assistance projects in the following sectors: 1. Energy (focusing on renewable energy and energy efficiency); 2. Infrastructure (water and sanitation, waste management, transportation and trade); 3. Urban planning and management; 4. Project presentation and finance.</narrative>
  </description>
